08/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski was in Luxembourg on Thursday (December 7th) for talks with his counterpart Jean-Claude Juncker.
The latter pledged full support for reforms in Macedonia, but declined to comment on a specific date for EU membership negotiations.
In other news Thursday, Gruevski invited the leaders of two main opposition parties, the Social Democratic Alliance for Macedonia and the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI), to nominate their representatives for the National Committee on NATO Accession.
He stressed that Macedonia is ready to double its efforts to meet NATO membership requirements.
(Albanian News - 08/12/06;
MIA, Makfax - 07/12/06)
